The paper deals with parallel algorithms for graph problems, specifically the maximum matching and minimum vertex cover problems. This suggests that the paper could belong to categories related to distributed computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), and graph theory (cs.GT). Among these, cs.DC and cs.DS seem to be the most likely categories, as the paper discusses parallel and distributed algorithms for graph problems. However, cs.DM, cs.CC, and cs.GT are also possible categories, as the paper deals with combinatorial optimization problems on graphs.
